<div class="element-wrap" data-label="Text Block" id="e-1605535867490" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1605535867490"><div class="elm text-edit"><p class="p1" style="text-align: left;">A gallery wall transforms a room and adds personality to your space, there are many ways that you can start a gallery wall and it can be a little daunting. First of all, ask yourself what kind of gallery wall you would like? Do you want a minimalistic, modern look with more of a uniform grid? Or do you want an electric look, experimenting with framing and textures? Once you’ve decided on this pick a colour palette that matches your interiors or interior style, by doing this all artwork added will look cohesive together, giving you more freedom on size and style!</p><p class="p1" style="text-align: left;">If you decide on the more minimalistic looks its best to hang your pictures in a grid layout, make sure that the outer frame edges stay aligned within the square or rectangle 'grid' perimeter. For a polished look its best to keep the spacing tight and use identical frames, this makes the gallery wall sleeker and lets the prints do the talking.</p><meta charset="utf-8"><p class="p1"><a href="https://nl.pinterest.com/pin/667940188480223539/?nic_v2=1a1kSRUXQ"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0400/8417/7060/files/At_Home_with_Framebridge_480x480.jpg?v=1603457919" alt="" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"></a></p><p class="p1" style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;Photo<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://theivorylane.com/2016/09/26/framebridge.html">theivorylane.com</a></p><p class="p1" style="text-align: center;"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0400/8417/7060/files/The_Easiest_Gallery_Wall_You_Could_Ever_Do_480x480.jpg?v=1603463053" alt=""></p><p class="p1" style="text-align: center;">Photo <a href="https://www.thecreativityexchange.com/2019/08/the-easiest-gallery-wall-you-could-ever-do.html">thecreativityexchange.com</a></p><p class="p1" style="text-align: left;">If you want an&nbsp;<span>eclectic</span> gallery wall and only have a few pieces of artwork, start with finding your favourite piece of art, add to the middle and build outwards, then fill in the gaps with the smaller items. Try mixing different frames and textures. If you have very small pieces of art or postcards, mount these on an oversized mat to create more of an impact</p><p class="p2" style="text-align: center;"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0400/8417/7060/files/Framebridge_on_Instagram__Gallery_Wall_Golden_Rule_2__Mind_the_Gaps_Generally_we_recommend_hanging_your_gallery_wall_frames_2_to_3_inches_apart__This_is_the_480x480.jpg?v=1603461019" alt=""></p><p class="p2" style="text-align: center;">Photo <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/CCbTc6op8VI/">Studiodiy</a></p><p class="p2" style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;<img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0400/8417/7060/files/how_to_create_a_gallery_wall_480x480.jpg?v=1603463437" alt=""></p><p class="p2" style="text-align: center;">Photo <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/CB8tRxdpYje/">@oxfordone</a></p><p class="p2" style="text-align: left;">You can get really creative and have a lot of fun! Don't be afraid to add other objects to the wall, such as mirrors, postcards, photographs, vinyl records, plates and even plants! Place them together on the floor and see how they work alongside each other. Once you have decided on the items fill in the gaps. If the wall gets a bit messy, line up the images on the top and bottom line, creating some horizontal continuously can make the wall look less crazy!</p><meta charset="utf-8"><p class="p2" style="text-align: center;"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0400/8417/7060/files/12_Reasons_to_Get_on_the_Ochre_Color_Trend_480x480.jpg?v=1603459701" alt=""></p><p class="p2" style="text-align: center;">Photo<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://www.instagram.com/nudeandthenovice/">@nudieandthenovice&nbsp;</a></p><p class="p2" style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;<img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0400/8417/7060/files/A_Super_Cute_Couple_Share_a_Soulful_Barcelona_Rental_480x480.jpg?v=1603463986" alt=""></p><p class="p2" style="text-align: center;">Photo<span>&nbsp;</span><a href="https://www.apartmenttherapy.com/house-tour-a-cozy-soulful-barcelona-rental-237009?utm_source=pinterest&amp;utm_medium=tracking&amp;utm_campaign=pinterest-gallery-share#6">apartmenttherapy.com</a></p><p class="p2" style="text-align: left;">Another popular way of hanging art is to use different sized shelves, as you won't have to commit and have the freedom to chop and change whenever you fancy! Adding shelves on top of each other gives the impression that the wall is mounted, this is great if you don't want to get the hammer out every time and can’t face measuring!</p><p class="p2" style="text-align: center;"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0400/8417/7060/files/Daily_Homes_480x480.jpg?v=1603462181" alt=""></p><p class="p2" style="text-align: center;">Photo Pinterest</p><p class="p2"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0400/8417/7060/files/minted_gallery_wall_480x480.jpg?v=1603461272" alt="" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"></p><p class="p2" style="text-align: center;">Photo&nbsp;<a href="https://isuwannee.com/2015/11/ive-got-99.html">isuwannee.com</a>&nbsp;</p><p class="p2" style="text-align: center;"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0400/8417/7060/files/DIY_Picture_Ledge_-_Jessica_Sara_Morris_480x480.jpg?v=1603462520" alt=""></p><p class="p2" style="text-align: center;">Photo <a href="https://www.whitepicketfarmhouse.com/diy-picture-ledge/">whitepicketfarmhouse.com&nbsp;</a></p><p class="p2" style="text-align: center;"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0400/8417/7060/files/Inside_Designer_Eliza_Gran_s_Bright_Los_Angeles_Home_480x480.jpg?v=1603461720" alt=""></p><p class="p2" style="text-align: center;">Photo&nbsp;<a href="https://www.lonny.com/Home+Tour/articles/AV8R4WXn4yf/Inside+Designer+Eliza+Gran+Bright+Los+Angeles">lonny.com</a></p><p class="p2" style="text-align: left;">We're aware that the price of all of the frames can add up (even if you’re buying from flea markets and IKEA) if you want a gallery wall but don't have the budget, simply use washi tape! We love this method, it can look incredibly chic and cool</p><p class="p2" style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;<img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0400/8417/7060/files/Screen_Shot_2020-10-23_at_16.46.10_480x480.png?v=1603464401" alt=""></p><p class="p2" style="text-align: center;">Photo <a href="https://honestlywtf.com/diy/diy-washi-tape-gallery-wall/">honestlywtf.com</a></p><p class="p2" style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;TIPS!</p><ul><li>As it is easy to get the measurements wrong, use brand strips as they are easy to remove if you want to change the art.</li></ul><ul><li>When hanging the art, start from the middle and work your way out. Make sure that each piece of art is an equal distance apart by using a tape measure.</li><li>After you hang a picture, remember to step back and check out your work! Making sure that you are happy to move onto the next picture.</li><li>Don’t worry if you make a mistake, especially if you are using brand strips. Just peel them away from the wall and start again!</li></ul><p class="p2">We have a Pinterest board dedicated to gallery walls, check it out for some more inspiration, and if you're looking for affordable artwork take a look at our dreamy posters on <a href="https://mooihome.store/search?type=product&amp;q=posters*">Mooi Home Store</a></p><p class="p2">Have fun with this and good luck!&nbsp;</p><p class="p2">&nbsp;</p><p class="p2">&nbsp;</p></div></div><!--gfsplit-->
